http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/Vaccination-camp/article14619904.ece

Vaccination for foot and mouth disease would be administered to over 70,000 cattle between September 1 and 21, Collector Sajjansingh R. Chavan said here on Thursday. Inaugurating 11th round of vaccination campaign, he said a total of 70350 cattle were identified. The veterinary specialists would give vaccination between 6 a.m. and 10 a.m. and 3 p.m. to 5 p.m. Regional Joint Director of Animal Husbandry Department Pinton Missier was present.